  "claim_short": "Under the source paper's nondegenerate Banach-space setup, the answer is no. If A^2_(m) is a Banach algebra, then for every a>0 the horizontal shift multiplier h_a(z)=exp(-az) lies in M(A^2_(m)) but not in A^2_(m)+C. Hence the multiplier algebra is strictly larger than the canonical unitization, so A^2_(m) is not a maximal ideal.",
